FT  09 JUN 92 / International Company News: H-P unveils small disk drive
HEWLETT-Packard, the computer and electronics group, unveiled the smallest
hard disk drive yet available, targeted at portable electronic products,
AP-DJ reports.
H-P said it expected the 1.3-inch drive to be used initially in hand-held
computers.
The new drive was developed through a joint effort with the AT&amp;T
Microelectronics, a unit of American Telephone &amp; Telegraph and Citizen Watch
of Japan, which will manufacture the product.
